TEXT 1768 32 Left 2 ;Please read the following notes carefully since the model behaves differently from the user interface for the LTM4739.\n \n(1) PMBus communication and memory address related functions and pins are not modeled.\n \n(2) Changes to parameter values while the simulation is running will not take effect unless the simulation is stopped\nand restarted. This is different from the way the part operates which will respond to the changes while running.\n \n(3) The following parameters can be defined by right-clicking on the LTM4739 symbol.\nThe nomenclature used here differs from the one in the data sheet. If any value of these parameters is set beyond the\nscope described in the data sheet, the resulting simulation will not be meaningful.\n \n     PMBUS_EN -- If PMBUS_EN = 0, then the pin-strap resistor values at PGM0 pin and PGM1 pin will be respected.\n                                    PGM0 resistor sets the POCP value.\n                                    PGM1 resistor sets the switching frequency and the six predefined scenarios.\n                            If PMBUS_EN = 1, then the following parameters will be respected: Freq, AMS, RVGA, POCP;\n     Vref -- in volt, sets reference voltage, in the range of [0.4V, 0.8V];\n     Freq -- in Hz, sets switching frequency as one of values of 500k, 600k, 750k, 1000k, 1200k, 2000k.\n                     PMBUS_EN needs to be set as 1, to make the value be in effect, otherwise, PGM1 is respected;\n     AMS -- If AMS = 0, then the AMS function is disabled.\n                 If AMS = 1, then the AMS function is enabled.\n                     PMBUS_EN needs to be set as 1, to make the value be in effect, otherwise, PGM1 is respected;\n     slope_comp -- in ampere, sets the slope compensation as one of the values of 840nA, 1260nA, 1680nA, 2100nA,\n                             2520nA, 2940nA, 3360nA, 3780nA;\n     RVGA -- in ohm, sets the voltage loop gain as one of the values of 10.1k, 11.1k, 15.7k, 22.7k, 26.8k, 31.3k, 37.3k,\n                   44.8k, 52.9k, 62.3k, 75k, 105.1k.\n                     PMBUS_EN needs to be set as 1, to make the value be in effect, otherwise, PGM1 is respected;\n     POCP -- in ampere, sets the peak over-current protection limit as one of the values of 9A, 11A, 13A, 15A.\n                     PMBUS_EN needs to be set as 1, to make the value be in effect, otherwise, PGM0 is respected;\n     voltage_loop_zero -- in Hz, sets the voltage loop zero frequency as one of the values of 3.22k, 5k, 7.6k, 8.85k,\n                                        10.6k, 12.5k, 15.2k, 17.7k;\n     tss -- in ms, sets the soft-startup time as one of the two values of 1ms (default) or 3ms;\n     DCM_EN -- sets the DCM operation of LTM4739:\n                        DCM_EN = 0: (default) Device is always at forced continuous conduction mode.\n                        DCM_EN = 1: DCM operation is enabled at light load.
